# Project Rules and Guidelines

## General Development Practices

### Code Quality
- Write clean, readable, and maintainable code
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add comments for complex logic or non-obvious behavior
- Follow PEP 8 style guide for Python code
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Avoid code duplication - refactor when patterns emerge

## File Organization
- Keep related code together
- Use appropriate directory structure for the project type
- Maintain clear separation of concerns

## Documentation
- Update documentation when adding new features
- Document API endpoints and command usage
- Keep README files up to date

## Error Handling
- Implement proper error handling for all user-facing features
- Provide clear error messages
- Log errors appropriately for debugging

## Performance
- Optimize code for performance when dealing with large datasets
- Consider memory usage when processing node data
- Avoid unnecessary operations in frequently called functions


## AI Assistant Guidelines
- Use the sequential MCP tool for reasoning when dealing with complex problems
- Prefer reading existing code before making changes
- Search the codebase to understand context before implementing features
- Ask for clarification if requirements are ambiguous

